<tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10704</anchor> <rss>erct-001O.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Lemma</taxon> <addr>erct-001O</addr>  <route>erct-001O.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>20</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Being a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">proposition</link> is a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">proposition</link></title>  <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-001O.agda" type="external">erct-001O.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>It is a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">proposition</link> that a given type <tex>A</tex> is a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">proposition</link>.</p>
 
   
   <tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="false" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10705</anchor>  <taxon>Proof</taxon>    <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>20</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors>   </frontmatter> <mainmatter>
  <p>To identify two witnesses <tex>\phi , \phi '  \colon   \mathchoice { \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x,y:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x,y:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x,y:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptscriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x,y:A \right ) \mathclose {} } } x = y</tex> that <tex>A</tex> is a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">proposition</link>, it suffices via the <link href="erct-0015.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0015" title="The univalence principle for dependent functions">pointwise univalent univalence principle for functions</link> to exhibit a double homotopy in <tex>A</tex> identifying each <tex>\phi  xy</tex> with <tex>\phi 'xy</tex>. As <link href="erct-001L.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001L" title="Propositions are sets">propositions are sets</link>, this follows from our assumption that <tex>A</tex> is a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">proposition</link>.</p>
</mainmatter> </tree>
 
</mainmatter> <backmatter><contributions/> <context><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10706</anchor> <rss>erct-003B.rss.xml</rss>  <addr>erct-003B</addr>  <route>erct-003B.xml</route> <date><year>2024</year> <month>1</month> <day>2</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Further closure properties of truncation levels</title>  </frontmatter> <mainmatter><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10707</anchor> <rss>erct-001M.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Lemma</taxon> <addr>erct-001M</addr>  <route>erct-001M.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>20</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Dependent sums of <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">propositions</link></title>  <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-001M.agda" type="external">erct-001M.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>If <tex>A</tex> is a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">proposition</link> and <tex>B \colon  A \to   \mathsf {Type}</tex> is a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">proposition</link>, then the dependent sum <tex>\mathchoice { \textstyle \sum _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \textstyle \sum _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptstyle \sum _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptscriptstyle \sum _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } } {Bx}</tex> is a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">proposition</link>.</p>
 
   
   <tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="false" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10708</anchor>  <taxon>Proof</taxon>    <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>20</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors>   </frontmatter> <mainmatter>
  <p>We fix pairs <tex>\mathopen {} \left ( a,b \right ) \mathclose {}</tex> and <tex>\mathopen {} \left ( a',b' \right ) \mathclose {}</tex> in <tex>\mathchoice { \textstyle \sum _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \textstyle \sum _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptstyle \sum _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptscriptstyle \sum _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } } {Bx}</tex>. By means of the <link href="erct-0018.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0018" title="The total path object of a displayed path object">total path object</link> on the <link href="erct-0017.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0017" title="The intrinsic opcleaving of a family of path objects">pointwise displayed path object</link> on <tex>B</tex>, it suffices to exhibit identifications <tex>p \colon  a = a'</tex> and <tex>p_* b = b'</tex>. These are given respectively by our assumptions that <tex>A</tex> and <tex>Ba'</tex> are <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">propositions</link>.</p>
</mainmatter> </tree>
 
</mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10709</anchor> <rss>erct-001N.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Lemma</taxon> <addr>erct-001N</addr>  <route>erct-001N.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>20</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Being <link href="erct-001H.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001H" title="Contractibility">contractible</link> is a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">proposition</link></title>  <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-001N.agda" type="external">erct-001N.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>It is a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">proposition</link> that a given type <tex>A</tex> is <link href="erct-001H.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001H" title="Contractibility">contractible</link>.</p>
 
   
   <tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="false" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10710</anchor>  <taxon>Proof</taxon>    <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>20</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors>   </frontmatter> <mainmatter>
  <p>Suppose we have two centres of contraction <tex>a,a':A</tex> with <tex>\chi _ \bullet \colon   \mathchoice { \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptscriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } } a = x</tex> and <tex>\chi '_ \bullet \colon \mathchoice { \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptscriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } } a'=x</tex> as witnesses of contraction. To identify <tex>\mathopen {} \left ( a, \chi _ \bullet \right ) \mathclose {}</tex> with <tex>\mathopen {} \left ( a', \chi '_ \bullet \right ) \mathclose {}</tex>, we employ the <link href="erct-0035.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0035" title="Covariant sum of an cocartesian family of path objects">covariant sum</link> of each of the <link href="erct-001C.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001C" title="Dependent product of path objects">pointwise path object</link> structures on <tex>\mathchoice { \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptscriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } } -=x</tex> over the <link href="erct-0013.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0013" title="The intrinsic path object">intrinsic path object</link> structure on <tex>A</tex>, constructing an identification <tex>p \colon  a = a'</tex> followed by a homotopy <tex>H  \colon   \mathopen {} \left ( \mathopen {} \left ( \chi _{a'} \right ) \mathclose {} _*^{ \mathchoice { \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptscriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } } -=x}  \chi _ \bullet \right ) \mathclose {}   \sim   \chi '_ \bullet</tex>. Fixing <tex>z \colon  A</tex>, we compute:</p>

  <tex display="block">
     \begin {aligned}
       \mathopen {} \left ( \mathopen {} \left ( \chi _{a'} \right ) \mathclose {} _*^{ \mathchoice { \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptscriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } } -=x}  \chi _ \bullet \right ) \mathclose {}  z
      &amp;=
       \mathopen {} \left ( \chi _{a'} \right ) \mathclose {} _*^{-=z}  \chi _z
       \\ 
      &amp;=
       \chi _{a'} ^{-1}   \cdot   \chi _z
       \\ 
      &amp;=  \chi '_z
     \end {aligned}
  </tex>

  <p>The first and second steps follow from general computation lemmas for transport, and the last step follows from the fact that <tex>A</tex> is a <link href="erct-001J.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001J" title="Sets">set</link>, which we may deduce as <link href="erct-001K.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001K" title="Contractible types are propositions">contractible types are propositions</link> and <link href="erct-001L.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001L" title="Propositions are sets">propositions are sets</link>.</p>
</mainmatter> </tree>
 
</mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10711</anchor> <rss>erct-001O.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Lemma</taxon> <addr>erct-001O</addr>  <route>erct-001O.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>20</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Being a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">proposition</link> is a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">proposition</link></title>  <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-001O.agda" type="external">erct-001O.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>It is a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">proposition</link> that a given type <tex>A</tex> is a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">proposition</link>.</p>
 
   
   <tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="false" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10712</anchor>  <taxon>Proof</taxon>    <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>20</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors>   </frontmatter> <mainmatter>
  <p>To identify two witnesses <tex>\phi , \phi '  \colon   \mathchoice { \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x,y:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x,y:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x,y:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptscriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x,y:A \right ) \mathclose {} } } x = y</tex> that <tex>A</tex> is a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">proposition</link>, it suffices via the <link href="erct-0015.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0015" title="The univalence principle for dependent functions">pointwise univalent univalence principle for functions</link> to exhibit a double homotopy in <tex>A</tex> identifying each <tex>\phi  xy</tex> with <tex>\phi 'xy</tex>. As <link href="erct-001L.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001L" title="Propositions are sets">propositions are sets</link>, this follows from our assumption that <tex>A</tex> is a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">proposition</link>.</p>
</mainmatter> </tree>
 
</mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10713</anchor> <rss>erct-001P.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Lemma</taxon> <addr>erct-001P</addr>  <route>erct-001P.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>20</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Being <link href="erct-001G.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001G" title="N-truncated type"><span style="white-space: nowrap"><tex>n</tex>-truncated</span></link> is a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">proposition</link></title>  <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-001P.agda" type="external">erct-001P.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>It is a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">proposition</link> that a given type <tex>A</tex> is <link href="erct-001G.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001G" title="N-truncated type"><span style="white-space: nowrap"><tex>n</tex>-truncated</span></link>.</p>
 
   
   <tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="false" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10714</anchor>  <taxon>Proof</taxon>    <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>20</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors>   </frontmatter> <mainmatter>
  <p>We proceed by induction on the <link href="erct-001F.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001F" title="Indexing of truncation levels">truncation level</link> <tex>n</tex>.</p>
  <ol><li>
      When <tex>n=-2</tex>, we recall from <ref addr="erct-001N" href="erct-001N.xml" taxon="Lemma"/> that being <link href="erct-001H.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001H" title="Contractibility">contractible</link> is a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">proposition</link>.
    </li>
    <li>
      When <tex>n=-1</tex>, we recall from <ref addr="erct-001O" href="erct-001O.xml" taxon="Lemma"/> that
      being a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">proposition</link> is a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">proposition</link>.
    </li>
    <li>
      For <tex>n  \geq  0</tex>, we assume by induction that being <span style="white-space: nowrap"><tex>n-1</tex>-truncated</span> is a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">proposition</link> to prove that being <span style="white-space: nowrap"><tex>n</tex>-truncated</span> is a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">proposition</link>. In other words, we must show that <tex>\mathchoice { \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x,y:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x,y:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x,y:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptscriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x,y:A \right ) \mathclose {} } } \mathsf {isTruncated} \, \mathopen {} \left ( n-1 \right ) \mathclose {} \, A</tex> is a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">proposition</link>. By our inductive hypothesis, this is a dependent product of <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">propositions</link> (<ref addr="erct-001B" href="erct-001B.xml" taxon="Corollary"/>).
    </li></ol>
</mainmatter> </tree>
 
</mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10715</anchor> <rss>erct-001U.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Lemma</taxon> <addr>erct-001U</addr>  <route>erct-001U.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>20</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Being an <link href="erct-001T.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001T" title="N-truncated map"><span style="white-space: nowrap"><tex>n</tex>-truncated</span> map</link> is a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">proposition</link></title>  <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-001U.agda" type="external">erct-001U.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>That a given map <tex>f \colon  A  \to  B</tex> is <span style="white-space: nowrap"><tex>n</tex>-truncated</span> is a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">proposition</link>.</p>
 
   
   <tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="false" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10716</anchor>  <taxon>Proof</taxon>    <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>20</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors>   </frontmatter> <mainmatter>
 <p>We must check that the product <tex>\mathchoice { \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:B \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:B \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:B \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptscriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:B \right ) \mathclose {} } } \mathsf {isTruncated} \, n \, \mathopen {} \left ( \mathsf {fiber} \, f \, x \right ) \mathclose {}</tex> is a <link href="erct-001T.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001T" title="N-truncated map">proposition</link>; indeed, this is a product of <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">propositions</link> (<ref addr="erct-001B" href="erct-001B.xml" taxon="Corollary"/>) as being an <link href="erct-001G.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001G" title="N-truncated type"><span style="white-space: nowrap"><tex>n</tex>-truncated</span> type</link> is a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">proposition</link> (<ref addr="erct-001P" href="erct-001P.xml" taxon="Lemma"/>).</p>
</mainmatter> </tree>
 
</mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10717</anchor> <rss>erct-002B.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Lemma</taxon> <addr>erct-002B</addr>  <route>erct-002B.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>27</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Being a <link href="erct-0029.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0029" title="Surjection">surjection</link> is a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">proposition</link></title>  <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-002B.agda" type="external">erct-002B.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>That a given map <tex>f \colon  E \to  B</tex> is <link href="erct-0029.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0029" title="Surjection">surjective</link> is a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">proposition</link>.</p>
 
   
   <tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="false" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10718</anchor>  <taxon>Proof</taxon>    <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>27</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors>   </frontmatter> <mainmatter>
 <p>By <ref addr="erct-001B" href="erct-001B.xml" taxon="Corollary"/>.</p>
</mainmatter> </tree>
 
</mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10719</anchor> <rss>erct-003G.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Corollary</taxon> <addr>erct-003G</addr>  <route>erct-003G.xml</route> <date><year>2024</year> <month>2</month> <day>10</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Being <link href="erct-003F.xml" type="local" addr="erct-003F" title="Bijection">bijective</link> is a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">proposition</link></title>  <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-003G.agda" type="external">erct-003G.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>That a given map <tex>f \colon  A  \to  B</tex> is <link href="erct-003F.xml" type="local" addr="erct-003F" title="Bijection">bijective</link> is a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">proposition</link>.</p>
 
   
   <tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="false" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10720</anchor>  <taxon>Proof</taxon>    <date><year>2024</year> <month>2</month> <day>10</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors>   </frontmatter> <mainmatter>
 <p>By <ref addr="erct-002B" href="erct-002B.xml" taxon="Lemma"/>, <ref addr="erct-001U" href="erct-001U.xml" taxon="Lemma"/> via <ref addr="erct-001M" href="erct-001M.xml" taxon="Lemma"/>.</p>
</mainmatter> </tree>
 
</mainmatter> </tree></mainmatter> </tree></context> <related><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10721</anchor> <rss>erct-001L.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Lemma</taxon> <addr>erct-001L</addr>  <route>erct-001L.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>20</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title><link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">Propositions</link> are <link href="erct-001J.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001J" title="Sets">sets</link></title>  <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-001L.agda" type="external">erct-001L.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>If a type <tex>A</tex> is a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">proposition</link>, then it is a <link href="erct-001J.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001J" title="Sets">set</link>.</p></mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10722</anchor> <rss>erct-001I.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>erct-001I</addr>  <route>erct-001I.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>20</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Proposition</title>  <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-001I.agda" type="external">erct-001I.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>A type <tex>A</tex> is said to be a <em><strong>proposition</strong></em> when every <tex>x:A</tex>, the type <tex>A</tex> is <link href="erct-001H.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001H" title="Contractibility">contractible with centre</link> <tex>x</tex>, i.e. all elements of <tex>A</tex> are identified.</p></mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10723</anchor> <rss>erct-0015.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Axiom</taxon> <addr>erct-0015</addr>  <route>erct-0015.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>19</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>The univalence principle for dependent functions</title>  <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-0015.agda" type="external">erct-0015.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>The reflexive graph structure on <tex>\mathchoice { \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptscriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } } {Bx}</tex> by <link href="erct-0014.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0014" title="Homotopy">homotopy</link> and <link href="erct-0014.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0014" title="Homotopy">identity homotopies</link> is <link href="erct-0010.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0010" title="Path object">univalent</link>.</p></mainmatter> </tree></related> <backlinks><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10724</anchor> <rss>erct-001P.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Lemma</taxon> <addr>erct-001P</addr>  <route>erct-001P.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>20</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Being <link href="erct-001G.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001G" title="N-truncated type"><span style="white-space: nowrap"><tex>n</tex>-truncated</span></link> is a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">proposition</link></title>  <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-001P.agda" type="external">erct-001P.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>It is a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">proposition</link> that a given type <tex>A</tex> is <link href="erct-001G.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001G" title="N-truncated type"><span style="white-space: nowrap"><tex>n</tex>-truncated</span></link>.</p>
 
   
   <tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="false" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10725</anchor>  <taxon>Proof</taxon>    <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>20</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors>  <parent>erct-001P</parent> </frontmatter> <mainmatter>
  <p>We proceed by induction on the <link href="erct-001F.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001F" title="Indexing of truncation levels">truncation level</link> <tex>n</tex>.</p>
  <ol><li>
      When <tex>n=-2</tex>, we recall from <ref addr="erct-001N" href="erct-001N.xml" taxon="Lemma"/> that being <link href="erct-001H.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001H" title="Contractibility">contractible</link> is a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">proposition</link>.
    </li>
    <li>
      When <tex>n=-1</tex>, we recall from <ref addr="erct-001O" href="erct-001O.xml" taxon="Lemma"/> that
      being a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">proposition</link> is a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">proposition</link>.
    </li>
    <li>
      For <tex>n  \geq  0</tex>, we assume by induction that being <span style="white-space: nowrap"><tex>n-1</tex>-truncated</span> is a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">proposition</link> to prove that being <span style="white-space: nowrap"><tex>n</tex>-truncated</span> is a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">proposition</link>. In other words, we must show that <tex>\mathchoice { \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x,y:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x,y:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x,y:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptscriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x,y:A \right ) \mathclose {} } } \mathsf {isTruncated} \, \mathopen {} \left ( n-1 \right ) \mathclose {} \, A</tex> is a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">proposition</link>. By our inductive hypothesis, this is a dependent product of <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">propositions</link> (<ref addr="erct-001B" href="erct-001B.xml" taxon="Corollary"/>).
    </li></ol>
</mainmatter> </tree>
 
</mainmatter> </tree></backlinks> <references/></backmatter></tree>